TY  - JOUR
TI  - Incentive Efficiency of Double Auctions
AU  - Wilson, Robert
AB  - [For a specified class of economic environments, a double auction in which numerous buyers and sellers submit sealed bids and offers is incentive efficient, in the sense that there is no other trading rule that is sure to be preferred by each agent, whatever his preferences.]
